HEADWORD: Tommy Atkins
<hw>Tom"my At"kins</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>Any white
regular soldier of the British army; also, such soldiers collectively;
-- said to be fictitious name inserted in the models given to soldiers
to guide them in filling out account blanks, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

